-- German real estate group IVG says investors approve debt swap
-- By Ludwig Burger
-- Thu Mar 20, 2014 12:25PM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, March 20 (Reuters) - The creditors and shareholders of Germany's IVG Immobilien <IVGG.DE>, the co-owner of London's landmark "Gherkin" tower, have approved the proposed debt-for-equity swap that will put the real estate firm in the hands of its creditors.

Creditors approved the plan with 99.5 percent of votes, while shareholders approved it with a 56.9 percent majority, the company said on Thursday.